The paper discusses a challenge on content-based video relevance prediction, which involves analyzing video content itself to predict relevance. This task falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of video frames, audio, subtitle, and metadata for prediction suggests computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) may also be relevant. Finally, the paper mentions the use of algorithms for development and evaluation, indicating machine learning (cs.LG) may also be applicable.
